      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "# Nexus Stream API Documentation\n\n## Endpoint: `/v1/stream`\n\n### Method: `POST`\n\n#### Description\nThe `/v1/stream` endpoint is designed to handle the creation and management of data streams. This endpoint provides the necessary functionality to initialize, configure, and control the data streams in your application.\n\n#### Parameters\n\n- `stream_id` (string, required): A unique identifier for the stream. This parameter is mandatory for the creation of a new stream.\n- `buffer_size` (integer, optional): Specifies the size of the buffer used for data storage. The default value is 1024. This parameter can be adjusted based on the application's requirements.\n- `auth_token` (string, required): A valid authentication token required to access the stream. This token must be provided in every request to ensure secure access.\n- `encryption_level` (string, optional): Defines the level of encryption to be applied to the stream data. The default value is `none`. Possible values are `low`, `medium`, and `high`.\n\n#### Responses\n\n- `200`: Success - The stream has been created successfully.\n- `401`: Unauthorized - The provided authentication token is invalid or missing.\n\n#### Example Request\n\n```http",
